introduction: 𝗨𝗻𝗹𝗼𝗰𝗸 𝗧𝗛𝗜𝗦 𝗟𝗘𝗦𝗦𝗢𝗡 𝗼𝗻 𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗔𝗽𝗽 𝗛𝗲𝗿𝗲 👉 📲 https://bit.ly/3H8Bw5Q Open on

vocabulary.definition: a more playful or casual way to say all right, used to acknowledge something or transition to the next part of a conversation
vocabulary.example: May I tell you what I think happened? All righty then.

vocabulary.definition: to be owned by someone or to be a possession of someone
vocabulary.example: These plates don't belong to me; there's been a mistake.

vocabulary.definition: to stress or give importance to something by pronouncing it more strongly
vocabulary.example: Well, as far as New York is concerned, you are the assman.

vocabulary.definition: to correct or resolve a confusing or mixed-up situation
vocabulary.example: I'm waiting for the Motor Vehicle Bureau to straighten out the license plate mix-up.

vocabulary.definition: to firmly establish someone or oneself in a place or position
vocabulary.example: Plant yourself there to hear the funniest stories from the proctologist.

vocabulary.definition: a very unlikely event or outcome, almost never happening
vocabulary.example: Every proctologist's story ends with 'It was a million to one shot, Doc.'
